title: Ignition crashes if you click anywhere on it at startup

content.raw:
This is not a huge problem, just a minor annoyance really. If I click anywhere on the main Ignition window before it finishes loading \(which is very easy to do on accident\), I get a crash with the stack trace below. This occurs with the newest available docker image.

It sometimes takes a bit of work to completely kill the remaining processes, but usually Ctrl\+C a bunch of times seems to work. An example launch command that caused this was `ign launch -v 4 tunnel_circuit_practice.ign robotName1:=X1 robotConfig1:=X1_SENSOR_CONFIG_1`.

This is not a huge problem, just a minor annoyance really. If I click anywhere on the main Ignition window before it finishes loading (which is very easy to do on accident), I get a crash with the stack trace below. This occurs with the newest available docker image.

It sometimes takes a bit of work to completely kill the remaining processes, but usually Ctrl+C a bunch of times seems to work. An example launch command that caused this was ign launch -v 4 tunnel_circuit_practice.ign robotName1:=X1 robotConfig1:=X1_SENSOR_CONFIG_1.
